<TITLE> Monsoon front crosses Indian coast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com)  A deep monsoon depression that has been brewing over the northwest Bay of Bengal crossed the Orissa-West Bengal Coast near Digha in India at around 7am, the met office said on Tuesday. It was lying over West Bengal and adjoining Orissa as a land depression, said the Meteorological Department in a special weather bulletin. All fishing boats and trawlers over the North Bay were advised to remain in shelter till further notice as squally weather may still hit the maritime ports and the coastal regions of Bangladesh. A steep pressure gradient was persisting over the north Bay. Under the influence of the depression, the low lying areas of Bangladesh's coastal districts were likely to be inundated by wind driven surges of two to four feet above the normal tide height, said the met office. The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been advised to keep hoisted local cautionary Signal-3
